article.headline: Texas A&M 74, Oklahoma State 52
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Takia Starks scored 16 points and
Morenike Atunrase added 15 as Texas A&M defeated Oklahoma State
74-52 in the Big 12 Conference opener for both teams.

Texas A&M (12-2, 1-0) jumped out to a 14-4 lead with 16:12 to
play in the first half and never trailed. The Aggies led by as much
as 25 points in the second half.

Starks and Atunrase each hit 6-of-13 from the field. Patrice
Reado came off the bench to score 10 points and had 11 rebounds for
Texas A&M.

Whitney Pegram led the Cowgirls (6-6, 0-1) with 12 points. Brisa
Silva added 10 points and had four steals, but also had 10
turnovers.

Texas A&M led 36-18 at the half.

The Aggies shot 37 percent from the field for the game. Oklahoma
State overcame a low-scoring first half to shoot 65 percent in the
second half.
